diff --git a/packages/opencode/src/session/prompt.ts b/packages/opencode/src/session/prompt.ts
index b3c3453..2b3b071 100644
--- a/packages/opencode/src/session/prompt.ts
+++ b/packages/opencode/src/session/prompt.ts
@@ -1510,6 +1510,36 @@ Goal: Write your final plan to the plan file (the only file you can edit).
 - Include the paths of critical files to be modified
 - Include a verification section describing how to test the changes end-to-end (run the code, use MCP tools, run tests)
 
+## TDD Todo Contract
+
+Before finalizing the plan, you MUST call \`todowrite\`.
+
+For implementation work, the todo list MUST include explicit TDD-oriented steps when applicable:
+1. confirm scope, files, and constraints
+2. identify existing tests or missing tests
+3. write or update failing tests first
+4. define or run the exact test command needed to confirm failure
+5. implement the minimal production change
+6. run tests to confirm success
+7. refactor or cleanup if needed
+8. provide execution handoff
+
+If the user provides pseudocode or a detailed implementation plan, preserve it faithfully.
+Do not silently rewrite the user's algorithm into a different one unless you explicitly call out the deviation and why it is necessary.
+
+The visible plan must match the todo list.
+Todos are the execution contract, not scratch notes.
+
+Structure the final plan so it can be rendered cleanly for the user:
+- start with \`# Goal\`
+- then \`# Plan Rationale\`
+- then \`# Actions\`
+- use \`## Step N: ...\` for each major step
+- in every major step include explicit \`What:\`, \`Why:\`, and \`Files/Tests:\` lines before the detailed bullets
+- keep the final summary concise enough that a rendered HTML view can generate anchors and a final summary table from those sections
+
+If the task is too small to require full TDD, say so explicitly and provide the lightest valid plan instead of forcing ceremony.
+
 ### Phase 5: Call plan_exit tool
